How the prices of the trips have evolved from 1989
Until 1989 there were in at that time Czechoslovakia only five state travel agencies authorized: Čedok, Sporturist, CKM, Rekrea and Autoturist.
The travel agencies of that one moment only sold in the majority of the cases trips to the socialist block, because the trips to the West were very restricted.
The Czech tourists went, therefore, of vacations to beaches of the GDR (German Democratic Republic), to the Soviet Union, (Sochi in Crimea in the Black Sea) to Bulgaria and Romania (both in the Black Sea) and to Hungary (Balaton).
A positive exception was the period between 1962 and 1972, when it was possible to be traveled to Yugoslavia, nevertheless, later the Yugoslav regime inclined towards the west and the trips of the Czech tourists then were restricted enough.
A great paradox of the socialism individually went the fact that to the citizens of the socialist block (that is, also to the Checoeslovacos) would not be allowed them to travel free and not even by the socialist countries.
If a citizen wanted to travel individually, for example, to Poland or the Soviet Union, he needed a letter invitation, if no, the individual trip were not possible.
The travel agencies also offered in those times trips to the West, but one was due to put to the tail with a sleeping bag and to happen all night thus, or to have “good well-known” in the agency.
Even so everything was not gained.
The call “change promise” that was the condition for the trips to the West, was not granted to the “people politically little trustworthy”, who thus could not travel absolutely.
The Czechoslovakian currency was not a convertible currency freely and, without change guarantee, it was not possible to obtain the resources (the western currency) to travel to the West.
The great majority of the Czechs spent their vacations in their own country, reason why there was a great number of cabins and houses of summer, that the Czechs acquired. This custom still persists.
The way to travel of the Czechs has suffered from 1989 an authentic revolution.
Whereas until 1989 for us he was does not go more to spend the vacations in the GDR or Bulgaria, the past year the Czechs made 4.5 million trips from vacations to countries worldwide.
Great paradox is nna, of which nowadays no longer we are conscious, the fact that to at the moment favorite destiny, the Croatia, until 1989 could not be traveled freely, because it comprised of at that time Yugoslavia.
At the beginning of years 90 the visa exemption prevailed to travel to the neighboring States of western Europe, which caused an enormous big wave of visits of short duration, coverall to Vienna or Germany.
The checoeslovacos, during long time, were not fed up with the excursions the West, everybody wanted to see it less for a moment.
For example, in Paris the groups of Czechs in the parks in tents slept, since our at that time income did not allow to pay to a hotel or pension us.
A typical characteristic of the Czechs of that one time was to take it with himself the food (conserves, inlays, etc.) to save.
Another important moment was the introduction of the convertibility of the Czech crown, thus our tourists could finally, after decades, to buy western currency freely.
Our standard of life also increased and him the average wages, which around 1997 brought about an increase in the demand of trips.
With the increase of the demand of trips the agencies began, as of 1997 with regularity, to prepare the trips using the connections of flights charter, which made to incredibly go down the prices of the trips in comparison with the past, thanks to the possibility of obtaining discounts by the volume of passengers.
At the end of the 90 of the last century, already the Czechs traveled without visa to almost all the developed countries, except EE.UU., which simplified our trips still more.
Another interesting moment in the history of the tourism pos-revolutionary happened already in the 2000, when it was organized, thanks to an enormous demand, the first direct flight from Czech Republic to an exotic country, and went to Thailand.
From that one year, they every year divide to direct flights charter with Czech tourists made distant and warm countries. This winter already will fly directly from Czech Republic to 12 exotic destinies.
The exotic countries at the moment visit them near 100 thousand Czechs the year.
Another interesting moment of this time, that symbolizes our development pos-revolutionary, arrived in 2008.
The 17 of November of 2008, EE.UU eliminated visas for the Czech tourists, and so our country happened to be more between the developed countries of the world.
In 2008 the Czechs, for the first time in their history, have happened more than half of their vacations abroad (50.3%) and for the first time in their history, have been spent in trips the foreigner more than 15 thousand Czech crowns by head, including the expenses in the stay site.
