Once the objective is fulfilled to reunite to 500 or 600 minors, the study will continue in the Sport Unit Independence (South of the Federal District) and finally in the Sport Unit Dwell them (to the north of the Federal District).
It explained that the intention of this investigation is to know the components and the importance the genetics with respect to the development of the obesity and of identifying in Mexican children and young people risk factors to prevent the appearance with degenerative diseases chronic.
When being celebrated this 14 of November the World-wide Day of the Diabetes, needed that the objective is to reunite to three thousand children and young people between six and 14 years of age, with the consent and supervision of its parents, for the application of specific questionnaires on feeding.
Also one will ask on the physical activity and antecedent heredofamiliares to them of diseases, in order to avoid risk factors that trigger sufferings like diabetes or renal insufficiency.
It detailed that Saturdays it is applied to all the participant anthropometric measurements (weight, size, circumference of waist), arterial ramming intake, genetic determination of the glucose levels, triglycerides, cholesterol and insulin and (looks for to identify genes that are associated to the infantile obesity).
Lopez cross indicated that this investigation obeys to the preoccupation of the professionals of the health by the alarming increase of weight in the minors.
“The surveys of health of 1999 and 2006 indicated that in only six years there was an increase, in the case of the children, of 77 percent in obesity, and the children of 47 percent\; in terms of overweight also a dramatic ascent was observed”, emphasized the specialist of the IMSS.
It indicated that the justification for the search of the markers is sustained in which the population of the country differs from others by its genetic history.
30 European percent informed that in average, the Mexican has 65 percent of American Indian inheritance, and five African percent and this condition are reflected in the genes that are associated to diabetes and excess of weight.
It explained that of general way, the genetics of the obesity is translated in the incapacity to burn the excess of energy that we consumed (calories) and that is stored in the form of fat.
The investigator explained that the direct benefit for the participants is the integral evaluation of the children, which allows to detect if they present some degree of overweight or obesity.
