The information is handled of confidential form, the doctors give it in writing to the parents, to those who it explains each one of the measurements and the changes to them in the lifestyle which they must realize to prevent diseases.
Lopez cross explained that three main components exist that cause overweight, obesity and other chronic sufferings: the sedentary lifestyle, that is the lack of daily physical activity, to most of remain the day seated in front of the television and to use means of transport instead of walking short distances.
Also the greater carbohydrate, sweetened drink consumption is due to the high caloric ingestion, that is to say, (tamales, bread, pizza, hamburger, et cetera) with lifted content in fats and proteins and the genetics that is analyzed in this protocol.
Asphalt of the UNAM would avoid pockets
Rafael Herrera, investigator of the Faculty of Chemistry of the UNAM, develops asphalts modified with polymers to produce a mixture with better performance, independent of the environmental conditions and of temperature
If the signals that sends the pavement were taken care of, it would not be necessary to repair near 200 thousand pockets every season of rains in the Metropolitan Zone of the Valley of Mexico, noticed Rafael Herrera Nájera, investigator of the Faculty of Química (FQ) of the UNAM, that assured that if the process of construction and maintenance of an asphalt pavement is the adapted one, the pockets could be reduced in amount or, even, be eliminated completely.
In its conference a technological opinion of the pockets, within the framework dictated of the Year the International of Chemistry, presented that the laboratory to its position develops asphalts modified with polymers to produce a mixture with similar characteristics to those of asphalt, but with a greater mechanical resistance, as much to high as to low temperatures.
Herrera Nájera considered that this modified asphalt type could be used in places where the climate is extremely hot, like some cities of the north of the country, to improve their performance and, therefore, the formation of pockets.
It explained that asphalt, the heaviest part of petroleum, is a hydrocarbon molecule set, some of high molecular weight, calls asphaltene, and others of low molecular weight, maltenos calls, that together give to the pavement their characteristic viscoelástico behavior him.
The viscoelástico behavior of the asphalt consists of which to high temperatures, near the 180 degrees, it behaves like a liquid, to 120 degrees Celsius his viscosity is very high and to 50 degrees Celsius it presents an almost solid state, whereas to very low temperatures, asphalt becomes fragile, added.
The previous thing means that in the streets the resistance of asphalt is not uniform, but is modified during the day in agreement with the environmental conditions and of temperature, it noticed the specialist in chemical engineering.
The investigator of the FQ observed that the streets of the City of Mexico in their majority are covered by flexible pavement, which is made up of six layers of materials, of which last the three involve to asphalt.
Between the most superficial layers is the asphalt folder, conformed by small stones bathed in asphalt and soon compacted.
Each one of the piedritas that the folder constitutes, aimed, is bathed with asphalt.
When journeying the vehicles and being generated efforts, this one allows that the forces spread very well in the pavement.
If one were modified asphalt would spread still better, the chemical engineer thought.
On the asphalt folder, it abounded, it is placed a last called layer tread folder, which is made of a fine material of stone, that is to say, a sand that also bathes in asphalt.
As one is the layer that is going to be in contact with the rims of the vehicles, it must have more mechanical force than the asphalt folder and provide friction in the way.
To the being the part of the pavement that is going to receive and to spread the efforts, the tread folder requires, also, to have the suitable thickness and the material is due to take care of del that is done.
The climate, especially the humidity and the variations of temperature, are also a factor very important to consider, especially the water, said, because it considerably affects the performance of the asphalt folder.
When the land becomes damp, the water spreads inside the folder and is difficult that it leaves, this causes a softening of all the layers of the pavement and, therefore, the formation of pockets.
In the process of formation of a pocket, it said, first in being worn away is the bearing film and only later the asphalt folder is affected, but the damage does not happen very instantaneously, but it is a process that would have to be taken care of the first signals with adapted maintenance programs.
The also member one of the National System of Investigators explained that the load to carry is another important factor in the formation of pockets and, for this reason, the thickness of each one of the layers of the pavement must always go in relation to the load to carry and to guarantee that it is fulfilled, to avoid that pockets form frequently.
Rafael Herrera warned that still there is much to investigate and to work on asphalt, for example, the asphalt emulsions, that in other countries already are even in the market and allow to repair the pockets with facility and without needing using high temperatures.
