The Nord Stream, new front door of the Russian gas in Europe
The gas pipeline Nord Stream, that western Europe with Russia communicates directly happening through the bottom of the Baltic Sea, has already been put in good condition.
It must provide gas to satisfy the needs with thirty million homes.
Gazprom, the Russian giant of the gas, has wanted to celebrate the event with great pomp.
The past Tuesdays, more than 500 guests, including four Government and Chiefs of State, participated to borders of the Baltic Sea, between the music of the orchestra and delicate bufet, in the inauguration of the Nord Stream, the new gas pipeline that communicates directly, under the sea, Russia with Germany.
Symbolically, the German Chancellor Angela Merkel, Russian President Dmitri Medvedev, French Prime minister François Fillon and his homologous one of the Netherlands, Mark Rutte, have turned together the steering wheel of the valve that controls the Russian gas entrance in the network of western Europe.
With this new gas pipeline, every year 27.5 million additional cubic meters will arrive from Russian gas at western Europe through a first one had of 1,224 km that communicate the region of Saint Petersburg with the Land of Mecklemburgo-Pomerania.
A second tube would have to conclude at the end of 2012 that will allow to provide a total of 55,000 million cubic meters of gas, that is to say, sufficient to cover all the French consumption.
In addition, already it is spoken of the possibility of constructing a third tube by the same route.
For Gazprom, the conclusion in time of this enormous work presents victory airs.
Poland and the Baltic countries had been against firmly to the project.
In fact, the Nord Stream is going to allow to provide to gas directly to Germany, avoiding the terrestrial course by third parties countries (Poland and the Ukraine).
Of blow, these two countries lose something of their power: for them, it will be more difficult to influence in Russia threatening closing it to him the access to the markets of western Europe.
In the algid point of the debate, Warsaw did not doubt in comparing the Nord Stream like a “new pact German-Soviet”, with reference to the alliance between Hitler and Stalin to occupy Poland in 1939.
That is to say, if the subject is politically delicate.
Western Europe, supporting the Russian project, has obtained a greater security of provision.
But the price is a weakening of the Europe of the energy, since the project has generated a breach between the European of the east and the west.
Russia has known, in only five years, to make prevail its vision over a direct alliance between Russia and the rich western countries, great consumers of gas and with some reserves more and more limited.
“This gas pipeline constitutes a component of our association with Russia, a new artery that unites to us of organic form”, François Fillon confirmed during the inauguration of the gas pipeline, demonstrating to what extent the great contracts of the sector of the gas are so politicians as economic.
All this explains the ample smiles in the faces of the managers of Gazprom, numerous in Lubmin, the destination of the gas.
The construction of this gas pipeline also supposes a technical profit.
The submarine tube is made of covered cement steel to protect it against the anchors of the ships.
One leans at heart of the sea, to an average of 200 ms of depth.
In order to construct it, it was necessary to avoid minefields that date from World War II.
“It was necessary to retire or to destroy a hundred of them, by precaution”, it indicates Jens Müller, spokesman of the society Nord Stream.
Also, it was necessary to carry far the measures of protection of the fauna and the flora.
The tube is one long metal serpent that weighs as 242 Eiffel towers and are not interrupted in all their length: neither by valves, nor by service stations.
A platform of control in waters of Sweden was predicted, but the people in charge of the project resigned to the same when seeing that the Swedish were very not prepared to allow that a Russian state society settled down permanently in the sea against its coasts.
“In case of failure, we will less than interrupt the passage of the gas in a minute”, precise Jens Müller.
In case of flight, the gas of the gas pipeline will be freed, therefore, to the atmosphere.
But the constructors consider probable little that a flight takes place, since they have anticipated junctions that, according to the forecasts, will be a flight every 100,000 years old.
The control of the state of the gas pipeline is guaranteed by means of a submarine robot, dragged by a ship, that inspection realizes outer, as well as by means of a device that circulates around the interior of the gas pipeline.
With the form of a pure one, it is introduced inside the tube, that owns a diameter of a meter, and it moves with the gas.
To its arrival, after three full working days of trip at a speed of three meters per second, it provides precise data on possible deformations of the metal.
The gas pipeline has been designed to work during fifty years without needing no type of repair.
The gas circulation is guaranteed simply by the pressure.
At the outset bars is of 200 and, when coming out of 100 bars.
Five companies have united their forces to be able to take to end this project.
The company leader is Gazprom, that owns 51% of participation.
To her, Germans E.ON and BASF were united (15.5% each), as well as the Dutch Gasunie and French group GDF Suez (9% each).
These five societies have created a company common, call Nord Stream, ordered to construct and to operate the gas pipeline.
It has its headquarters in Zoug, Switzerland, where the imposition is especially favorable.
Later, Gazprom rented to this society, during a renewable term of twenty-five years, the totality of the cargo capacities of gas.
“To Gazprom it will pay to him by the total capacity, independent of the amount of gas that really transport”, precise Jens Müller.
The financing of the construction of the gas pipeline has taken I finish in a 30% with the contribution of the shareholders and in a 70% by means of bank loans.
The total cost of the work would have to both reach 7,400 million Euros after tubes.
After GDF Suez, for example, the investment has reached 240 million.
But the minority shareholders are sure that they will not surpass his investment, since Gazprom by itself assumes the risk of the expenses.
The gas pipeline emerges from the Baltic Sea in Lubmin, in a planted sandy coast of pines.
Some valves, with 4.5 meters of height, form the door of exit of the gas.
Some sensorial exist that measure the pressure, the temperature and the specific features of the gas to the arrival, before German transfers itself to the gas pipelines.
From the past Tuesday, the terminal hourly receives a million cubic meters of Russian gas.
To total capacity, they will be three million per hour and in 2012, six million.
